## 1. Project Overview

Acme Retail receives ~18,000 customer interactions per day. AtlasCare is an autonomous AI agent that resolves Tier-1 queries without human intervention — tracking orders, cancelling items, processing refunds, updating addresses, and enforcing business rules (e.g., auto-refund cap of ₹25,000).

Refer to [`Architecture.md`](Architecture.md) for the complete Architecture documentation.
 
 

### Core Capabilities

| Capability | Description |
|---|---|
| **Order Tracking** | Fetches real-time order status and tracking details from OMS |
| **Partial Cancellation & Refund** | Cancels individual line items and initiates refunds within policy limits |
| **Address Update** | Updates shipping address on active orders or profile address in CRM |
| **Escalation with Audit Trail** | Detects refunds above ₹25,000 threshold, creates a CRM case, and holds without touching the Payments tool |
| **Policy Q&A** | Answers questions about return windows, refund SLAs, and platform rules from the Knowledge Base |
| **SSO Login** | Secure Auth0-based login; user identity is verified on every API call |
| **Admin Dashboard** | Real-time operational KPIs, token usage trends, query intent distribution, and escalation queue management |

<br>

## 2. Technology Stack


| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Frontend** | React 23.11 + Vite | Chat UI, Metrics Dashboard |
| **Auth** | Auth0 (SPA + API) | SSO login, JWT issuance |
| **HTTP Client** | Axios | Frontend → Backend API calls |
| **Charts** | Recharts | Token trends, intent pie chart |
| **Backend** | FastAPI + Uvicorn | REST API server |
| **Agent Framework** | LangGraph | Stateful ReAct agent graph |
| **LLM** | Groq (llama-3.3-70b-versatile) | Reasoning and tool invocation |
| **LLM Client** | LangChain-Groq | LangChain wrapper for Groq |
| **Database** | SQLite | Persistent order, customer, case, and metrics state |
| **JWT Validation** | python-jose | Auth0 RS256 token verification |
| **Logging** | Python logging (RotatingFileHandler) | Structured application logs |


<br>

