## 6. Installation & Running the Application

### Prerequisites

| Requirement | Version | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Python | 3.10, 3.11, or 3.12 | Python 3.11 recommended (matches .pyc files in repo) |
| Node.js | 18+ | Required to run the Vite frontend |
| npm | 9+ | Comes with Node.js |
| Git | Any | To clone the repo |

### Step 1 — Clone / Extract the Project

```bash
# If you have the zip:
unzip chitrak_aseri_46561.zip
cd chitrak_aseri_46561
```

### Step 2 — Create and Configure the `.env` File

> **Critical**: The `.env` filed already exists and Users just need to replace the Placeholder value with their actual GROQ API Keys.

### Step 3 — Install Python Dependencies

This installs all pinned Python packages including: `fastapi`, `uvicorn`, `langchain-groq`, `langgraph`, `langgraph-checkpoint`, `python-dotenv`, `python-jose`, `httpx`, and more.

**Tip for virtual environments** (recommended):
> ```bash
> python -m venv venv
> source venv/bin/activate        # macOS/Linux
> venv\Scripts\activate           # Windows
> pip install -r requirements.txt
> ```

### Step 4 — Install Frontend Dependencies

```bash
# Navigate into the frontend directory
cd frontend
npm install
cd ..        # Return to project root
```

This installs React, Auth0, Axios, Recharts, Vite, and all other frontend packages into `frontend/node_modules/`.

### Step 5 — Run the Application

```bash
# From the project root directory
python main.py
```

This single command:
1. Starts the FastAPI backend server on `http://127.0.0.1:8000`
2. Starts the Vite frontend dev server on `http://localhost:5173`
3. Automatically opens `http://localhost:5173` in your browser after 2 seconds

**Expected console output:**
```
[INFO] 🚀 Booting up the AtlasCare React Frontend...
[INFO] ⚡ Starting the FastAPI Backend Server on port 8080...
[INFO] 🌐 Opening AtlasCare in your default web browser...
INFO:     Started server process [XXXXX]
INFO:     Uvicorn running on http://127.0.0.1:8000 (Press CTRL+C to quit)
```

<br>

### Running Frontend and Backend Separately (Alternative)

If `python main.py` doesn't auto-open the browser or you want separate terminals:

**Terminal 1 — Backend:**
```bash
uvicorn main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000 --reload
```

**Terminal 2 — Frontend:**
```bash
cd frontend
npm run dev
```

Then open `http://localhost:5173` manually.

<br>

## 7. Authentication & User Personas

AtlasCare uses **Auth0** as the SSO provider. Two persona types are supported:

### User Persona (Default)
- Sees only the **Chat** interface
- Can track orders, cancel items, request refunds, update information
- Cannot access the Metrics Dashboard
- All data access is scoped to their own account (email → customer_id mapping enforced in every tool)

### Admin Persona
- Sees both **Chat** and **Metrics** tabs in the navigation bar
- Can view the Operational Dashboard: KPI cards, token usage trends, intent distribution, and the Human Specialist Queue
- Can click **"Mark as Done"** to resolve escalation cases
- Admin detection: the app checks for `https://atlascare.com/roles` = `["admin"]` in the JWT claims.





<br>

